LAGOS – Dr Tunde Moses Elebute, a public affairs commen­tator and human rights promoter, has hailed the number of presidential contenders that have so far announced their in­tensions so far. Elebute, Deputy Direc­tor, Crime Victims Foun­dation of Nigeria (CRIVI­FON), Lagos State chapter, who spoke to Sunday Inde­pendent in Lagos on Satur­day, said with the presiden­tial contenders that have emerged so far, Nigerians will have good materials to choose from when the elec­tion proper comes. Among those who have announced their intentions so far, included former La­gos State governor, Senator Bola Ahmed Tinubu; for­mer Abia State governor, Senator Orji UzorKalu; Eb­onyi State governor, David Umahi, and Kogi State gov­ernor, Yahaya Belo, all of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC). Leaders’ Honesty Will Check Security Challenges – Bishop Eichie IPOB Allays Fears Of Lockdown In South-East, Announces… From the main opposi­tion Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), former Senate President and ex-Secretary of the Government of the Federation (SDF), Anyim Pius Anyim, Senator Mao Ohuabunwa, Dr. Doyin Okupe and Dele Momodu, publisher of Ovation Mag­azine, have also indicated interest in the nation’s number position. Elebute stated: “The number of the contend­ers gives us many options from which the parties can choose their flag bearers. After the primary, the num­ber will scale down. “It also shows that eth­nicity and tribal senti­ments are still very much with us. This time around, I am trusting God to influ­ence the hearts of Nige­rians to choose a correct leader.